In simple terms 

Pulse Sequence = Instructions for the MRI scanner

A pulse sequence is a carefully timed series of:
	•	Radiofrequency (RF) pulses
	•	Magnetic field gradients
	•	Signal acquisition windows

These elements control how nuclear spins behave and how signals are measured.

A pulse sequence tells the scanner:
	•	when to excite spins
	•	when to refocus signals
	•	when to measure the signal
	•	how to encode spatial information